body_html:
@HackersSpirit The Windows build was broken for a while, can you sync to HEAD and try the build again?

Looks like you are using the prebuilt TF library in CMake, some APIs may not be available this way. The Bazel way in https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/extend/cc should work better.

bazel run -c opt //tensorflow/cc/example:example
body:
@HackersSpirit The Windows build was broken for a while, can you sync to HEAD and try the build again?

Looks like you are using the prebuilt TF library in CMake, some APIs may not be available this way. The Bazel way in https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/extend/cc should work better.
```
bazel run -c opt //tensorflow/cc/example:example
```
